																						<dt><a name="anchor110274"></a><font size="-1" face="Arial">9 This piece, which later became immensely popular with early American theatregoers, was founded on a novel called <u>English Adventures</u>. It was one of the two plays (the other being <i>Venice Preserved</i>) which gained for Thomas Otway the high rank he holds among the tragic poets of the Restoration. Notwithstanding his success, the author ended his days in the most abject poverty. The story goes that he almost choked to death while ravenously swallowing a crust of bread thrown to him by a passing stranger.</font>
